[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":324},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fhow-to-resolve-github-conflicts\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fhow-to-resolve-github-conflicts\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fhow-to-resolve-github-conflicts\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fhow-to-resolve-github-conflicts\u002F":299,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fhow-to-resolve-github-conflicts\u002F":308},"\u002Fgit\u002F20190621\u002F4239571950\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":283,"date":284,"description":19,"extension":285,"lang":286,"meta":287,"navigation":288,"path":289,"readingMinutes":290,"seo":291,"standalone":292,"stem":293,"tags":294,"tldr":296,"updated":296,"url":297,"__hash__":298},"content\u002Fen\u002FGit\u002Fhow-to-resolve-github-conflicts.md","How to Resolve GitHub Conflicts","9504123957",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":274},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,37,40,70,73,77,80,87,90,95,98,104,107,124,131,146,152,156,159,168,171,177,184,190,195,201,207,212,219,225,230,233,237,240,262,265,270],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"When you're working on a team project, code conflicts come up pretty easily. So this post walks through how to actually resolve them.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"setup","Setup",[17,25,26,27,31,32,36],{},"Before we can resolve a conflict, we need to ",[28,29,30],"strong",{},"make one",". Don't worry — you read that right. The only way to learn is to break things first. (After doing this a few times you'll know exactly how to ",[33,34,35],"del",{},"maliciously cause conflicts for your coworkers",".)",[17,38,39],{},"I'm reusing this same demo project:",[41,42,43,54,62],"ul",{},[44,45,46,47],"li",{},"Project I'm interested in: ",[48,49,53],"a",{"href":50,"rel":51},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fjc-eng\u002Ftest-repos",[52],"nofollow","test-repos",[44,55,56,57],{},"Project owner: ",[48,58,61],{"href":59,"rel":60},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fjc-eng",[52],"jc-eng (my alt account)",[44,63,64,65],{},"Collaborator: ",[48,66,69],{"href":67,"rel":68},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhsiangfeng",[52],"me",[17,71,72],{},"Why do conflicts happen in the first place? Git conflicts mostly come from multiple people editing the same file at the same time. So in team projects, people usually communicate and try to avoid touching the same file. But sometimes you can't avoid it — and that's when you need to know how to resolve.",[12,74,76],{"id":75},"resolving-the-conflict","Resolving the conflict",[17,78,79],{},"I'll fast-forward straight to the conflict. After we forked and cloned the project, made our changes, and tried to open a PR back to the original — boom, conflict.",[17,81,82],{},[83,84],"img",{"alt":85,"src":86},"Conflict","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FPnT5AAK.png",[17,88,89],{},"Now we need to fix up our cloned project's Git state. Let's walk through it step by step.",[91,92,94],"h3",{"id":93},"step-1-set-up-the-upstream","Step 1: Set up the upstream",[17,96,97],{},"Open the original project's repo and copy its clone URL.",[17,99,100],{},[83,101],{"alt":102,"src":103},"Image","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FY9hmSbY.png",[17,105,106],{},"Then in your terminal, run:",[108,109,114],"pre",{"className":110,"code":111,"language":112,"meta":113,"style":113},"language-git shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","git remote add upstream https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fjc-eng\u002Ftest-repos.git\n","git","",[115,116,117],"code",{"__ignoreMap":113},[118,119,122],"span",{"class":120,"line":121},"line",1,[118,123,111],{},[17,125,126,127,130],{},"That's ",[115,128,129],{},"git remote add [remote-name] [remote-url]",".",[17,132,133,134,137,138,141,142,145],{},"You can now run ",[115,135,136],{},"git remote"," to see which remotes you have. (",[115,139,140],{},"upstream"," is the original project, ",[115,143,144],{},"origin"," is your fork.)",[17,147,148],{},[83,149],{"alt":150,"src":151},"Remotes","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FuWWaYIQ.png",[91,153,155],{"id":154},"step-2-update-from-upstream","Step 2: Update from upstream",[17,157,158],{},"The reason our PR back to the original triggered a conflict is that our local is out of date. So we need to pull from upstream:",[108,160,162],{"className":110,"code":161,"language":112,"meta":113,"style":113},"git pull upstream master\n",[115,163,164],{"__ignoreMap":113},[118,165,166],{"class":120,"line":121},[118,167,161],{},[17,169,170],{},"You'll then see this screen.",[17,172,173],{},[83,174],{"alt":175,"src":176},"Pull project","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Fh150Nuy.png",[17,178,179,180,183],{},"If you want to keep ",[28,181,182],{},"both"," sets of changes, click \"Accept Both Changes\" — both versions stay.",[17,185,186],{},[83,187],{"alt":188,"src":189},"Accept Both Changes","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FdmCMS0y.png",[17,191,192],{},[83,193],{"alt":188,"src":194},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FD1bdIRP.png",[17,196,179,197,200],{},[28,198,199],{},"theirs",", click \"Accept Incoming Change\".",[17,202,203],{},[83,204],{"alt":205,"src":206},"Accept Incoming Change","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FeJGrgtA.png",[17,208,209],{},[83,210],{"alt":205,"src":211},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FhpBi5Rx.png",[17,213,214,215,218],{},"And if (so many ifs) you want to keep ",[28,216,217],{},"yours"," instead of theirs, click \"Accept Current Change\".",[17,220,221],{},[83,222],{"alt":223,"src":224},"Accept Current Change","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FS07ZZJq.png",[17,226,227],{},[83,228],{"alt":223,"src":229},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FyHs0vux.png",[17,231,232],{},"(Most of the time you'll go with \"Accept Both Changes\".)",[91,234,236],{"id":235},"final-step-push-back-to-your-fork","Final step: Push back to your fork",[17,238,239],{},"Once you've fixed the conflict, push back to your own repo:",[108,241,243],{"className":110,"code":242,"language":112,"meta":113,"style":113},"git add .\ngit commit -m 'resolve conflict'\ngit push origin master\n",[115,244,245,250,256],{"__ignoreMap":113},[118,246,247],{"class":120,"line":121},[118,248,249],{},"git add .\n",[118,251,253],{"class":120,"line":252},2,[118,254,255],{},"git commit -m 'resolve conflict'\n",[118,257,259],{"class":120,"line":258},3,[118,260,261],{},"git push origin master\n",[17,263,264],{},"Now try sending the PR again — the conflict's gone and it merges cleanly.",[17,266,267],{},[83,268],{"alt":102,"src":269},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FzM2oPd0.png",[271,272,273],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":113,"searchDepth":252,"depth":252,"links":275},[276,277,278],{"id":14,"depth":252,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":252,"text":23},{"id":75,"depth":252,"text":76,"children":279},[280,281,282],{"id":93,"depth":258,"text":94},{"id":154,"depth":258,"text":155},{"id":235,"depth":258,"text":236},"Git","2019-06-21 16:35:09","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002Fhow-to-resolve-github-conflicts","2",{"title":6,"description":19},false,"en\u002FGit\u002Fhow-to-resolve-github-conflicts",[295,283],"GitHub",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fhow-to-resolve-github-conflicts\u002F","5eSN4hh_xhSV_BmVPFRh2WXB5o35yBh1aaKR7aGHEVw",{"newer":300,"older":304},{"url":301,"title":302,"date":303},"\u002Fen\u002Ftypescript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F22\u002Fts-fundamentals-variables\u002F","TypeScript Fundamentals — Variables","2019-06-22 15:06:22",{"url":305,"title":306,"date":307},"\u002Fen\u002Fjavascript\u002F2019\u002F06\u002F21\u002Fcoffeescript-ternary-operator\u002F","How Do You Write a Ternary Operator in CoffeeScript? (Spoiler: You Don't)","2019-06-21 11:49:07",[309,314,319],{"url":310,"title":311,"date":312,"readingMinutes":313},"\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2026\u002F02\u002F26\u002Fgit-push-force-with-lease-better-than-force\u002F","A Safer Alternative to git push --force: git push --force-with-lease","2026-02-26 09:39:40","4",{"url":315,"title":316,"date":317,"readingMinutes":318},"\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2026\u002F01\u002F22\u002Fgit-default-branch-master-to-main\u002F","Git init Shows a master Branch Hint? Here's How to Set main as Default","2026-01-22 16:20:40","3",{"url":320,"title":321,"date":322,"readingMinutes":323},"\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2026\u002F01\u002F21\u002Fgit-worktree-multiple-ai-agents-one-project\u002F","What Is Git Worktree? The Secret to Running Multiple AI Agents in One Project","2026-01-21 16:04:27","5",1784020351049]